@emoya-cmyk/compaction

The lossless tabular-compaction approach (array-of-objects reformatted into one
schema header + delimited rows) is inspired by the "lossless compaction" primitive
in chopratejas/headroom (https://github.com/chopratejas/headroom), licensed
Apache-2.0.

This module is a clean-room re-implementation of ONLY that one lossless idea, from
a written spec, in our own languages (JavaScript + Python). No Headroom source was
copied. The lossy capabilities Headroom also provides — row-drop / item truncation,
CCR reversible-offload with TTL retrieval, and opaque-blob value substitution — are
deliberately NOT reproduced here: they are structurally incompatible with this
family's grounded-AI invariant (no asserted figure may derive from an altered or
truncated set).

This credit is provided as good practice; a clean-room re-implementation of an
unprotectable idea carries no license obligation of its own.
